    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i also saw a section about how blockages in the tube can cause the airspeed indicator to fail or give wrong readings. what kind of things usually cause those blockages? is it just debris or something else?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Common causes of blockages in the pitot tube include ice buildup, dirt, debris, and debris from preventer tubes, as well as mold and mildew accumulation if the tube is not heated or purified. Additionally, other contaminants like water, smoke, or ambient air can also cause issues. Aircraft often have a heat element in the pitot tube to prevent blockages, but maintenance is still essential to ensure its operation.",
      "source": "target",
